[SN]TITLE[SN]
Kyle McAllister: Derby County sign St Mirren winger for undisclosed fee

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Derby County have signed teenage Scottish winger Kyle McAllister from St Mirren for an undisclosed fee.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 18-year-old, who made his debut for the Scottish Championship club in February 2016 less than a month after his 17th birthday, has signed a three-and-a-half-year contract.
Scotland youth international McAllister has played 14 games this season, scoring one goal.
Rams manager Steve McClaren said McAllister is one for "the future".
He said: "Kyle turned 18 last week, so now we have him on board we will look to develop him."
